Task 3

The qualitative variables in ddt are river and species.

The quantitative variables in ddt are mile, length, weight, and DDT.

Theres 3 types of species in the dataset which are CCATFISH, LMBASS, SMBUFFALO

# LMBASS with WEIGHT > 800
subset(ddt, SPECIES == "LMBASS" & WEIGHT > 800)
##     RIVER MILE SPECIES LENGTH WEIGHT DDT
## 141   TRM  345  LMBASS     30    856 2.2
## 144   TRM  345  LMBASS     36   1433 1.9
# RIVER is SCM and DDT > 4.0
subset(ddt, RIVER == "SCM" & DDT > 4.0)
##    RIVER MILE  SPECIES LENGTH WEIGHT DDT
## 16   SCM    1 CCATFISH     45    984 9.1
## 17   SCM    1 CCATFISH     43    965 7.8
## 18   SCM    1 CCATFISH     45   1084 4.1

TASK 5

## Task 5  tables and barplots



# 1) Table of rivers
river_tab <- table(ddt$RIVER)
river_tab
## 
## FCM LCM SCM TRM 
##   6   6   6 126
# 2) Color-coded barplot of rivers
barplot(
  river_tab,
  col = rainbow(length(river_tab)),
  main = "Fish counts by River",
  xlab = "River",
  ylab = "Count"
)

# 3) Table of rivers crossed with species
riv_species <- table(ddt$RIVER, ddt$SPECIES)   # rows: RIVER, cols: SPECIES
riv_species
##      
##       CCATFISH LMBASS SMBUFFALO
##   FCM        6      0         0
##   LCM        6      0         0
##   SCM        6      0         0
##   TRM       78     12        36
# 4) Barplot of rivers crossed with species (grouped bars + legend)
cols <- rainbow(nrow(riv_species))
barplot(
  riv_species,
  beside = TRUE,                 # grouped bars (set FALSE for stacked)
  col = cols,
  main = "Counts: River  Species",
  xlab = "Species",
  ylab = "Count"
)
legend("topright", legend = rownames(riv_species), fill = cols, bty = "n", cex = 0.8)

## Task 7  Boxplot of DDT
boxplot(ddt$DDT, main = "DDT", ylab = "DDT")

## Task 7  Boxplot of WEIGHT
boxplot(ddt$WEIGHT, main = "WEIGHT", ylab = "WEIGHT")

## Task 7  Boxplot of LENGTH

Task 8

ddt$RIVER <- factor(ddt$RIVER)

coplot(LENGTH ~ WEIGHT | RIVER,
       data = ddt,
       number = 1, overlap = 0,
       xlab = "WEIGHT", ylab = "LENGTH",
       main = "LENGTH vs WEIGHT by RIVER")

ddt$SPECIES <- factor(ddt$SPECIES)
coplot(DDT ~ WEIGHT | SPECIES,
       data = ddt,
       number = 1, overlap = 0,
       xlab = "WEIGHT", ylab = "DDT",
       main = "DDT vs WEIGHT by SPECIES")

TASK 9

library(ggplot2)

ggplot(ddt, aes(x = SPECIES, y = WEIGHT, fill = RIVER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ggtitle("Ruben Oso") +
  xlab("SPECIES") +
  ylab("WEIGHT")

ggplot(ddt, aes(x = RIVER, y = LENGTH, fill = SPECIES)) +
  geom_violin(position = "dodge") +
  ggtitle("Ruben Oso") +
  xlab("RIVER") +
  ylab("LENGTH")

ggplot(ddt, aes(x = WEIGHT, y = LENGTH, color = SPECIES)) +
  geom_point() +
  ggtitle("Ruben Oso") +
  xlab("WEIGHT") +
  ylab("LENGTH")
